<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
     PROBLEM → SOLUTION
════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="pvh-problem" aria-label="Problem and solution">
  <div class="pvh-problem-inner">
    <div class="pvh-problem-col" data-pvh-enter>
      <span class="pvh-tag">The hidden problem</span>
      <h2 class="pvh-problem-heading">Cats weren't built to drink from bowls.</h2>
      <p class="pvh-problem-body">They descend from desert ancestors who drank from running streams — never standing pools. Stagnant water registers as potentially contaminated to their senses. Most cats drink just enough to get by, not enough to thrive. The result is chronic mild dehydration that quietly damages kidneys over years, often going unnoticed until it's a serious problem.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pvh-problem-col pvh-problem-col--solution" data-pvh-enter style="transition-delay:0.12s">
      <span class="pvh-tag" style="color:var(--pvh-green-mid);">The fix</span>
      <h2 class="pvh-problem-heading">Brook gives them the running water they actually want.</h2>
      <p class="pvh-problem-body">A constant, gentle flow of filtered, oxygenated water — quiet enough that cats come back to it on their own, without prompting. Most owners notice their cat drinking from Brook within the first day. More water in means more health out. It's the simplest upgrade you can make for a cat who lives primarily indoors.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
     HOW IT WORKS
════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="pvh-steps" id="pvh-how-it-works" aria-label="How Brook works">
  <div class="pvh-steps-inner">
    <div class="pvh-section-header" data-pvh-enter>
      <span class="pvh-tag">How it works</span>
      <h2 class="pvh-section-title">Three steps. That's it.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="pvh-steps-grid">
      <div class="pvh-step" data-pvh-enter>
        <div class="pvh-step-num">Step 01</div>
        <h3 class="pvh-step-title">Fill the reservoir</h3>
        <p class="pvh-step-body">Fill Brook's 2-litre ceramic reservoir from the tap. The whole thing takes about 20 seconds. Most cats get 7–10 days between refills.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pvh-step" data-pvh-enter style="transition-delay:0.1s">
        <div class="pvh-step-num">Step 02</div>
        <h3 class="pvh-step-title">Plug it in</h3>
        <p class="pvh-step-body">The whisper-quiet pump circulates water through the triple-stage filter, 24 hours a day, under 25 decibels. Your home stays quiet; your cat stays hydrated.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pvh-step" data-pvh-enter style="transition-delay:0.2s">
        <div class="pvh-step-num">Step 03</div>
        <h3 class="pvh-step-title">Walk away</h3>
        <p class="pvh-step-body">Refill every 7–10 days. Replace the filter once a month. Brook handles the rest — continuously, silently, reliably.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

